NEW YEARS EVE, 2022.
I could rave on about what I’ve achieved in 2022 and what I plan on doing next year and blah blah blah.... but it’s pointless.
Because as the year comes to an end I always reflect on its lessons.
And 2022 had many..... but the most important one I learnt, and probably THE most important one I’ll EVER learn, is the realisation that less is more.
Less stress.
Less drama.
Less noise.
Less pressure of expectation.
Less comparison.
Less words.
Less possessions.
Less social media.
Less worry.
Less preconceived ideas of what I’m “supposed” to write.
Less ideals on what success is.
Less judgement.
LESS IS MORE.
Self care is my new KPI.
And the things I want more of..... peace, vulnerability, happiness, friendship and love. 
Being in the moment.
Time with my family and friends.
So this is me.... being in the moment.
Thank you for being my friend on facebook and Instagram. Thank you for being so supportive and believing in me when I sometimes forget to believe in myself.
Thank you for just being you..... because being you is pretty amazing.
Happy New Year my beloved friends.
You are adored ❤️

As the clocks begin to tick over to the 16th of March, Miles Ever After goes live in the first country, Australia in just four hours.
😱😱😱😱😱😱😱
I will be making a discussion group and I beg of you.
NO SPOILERS POSTED ANYWHERE outside of that group PLEASE!!!!
Please let everybody have that first time read excited rush experience that you get to have.
There’s a reason I don’t name a trope on my books, or a “HEA” label.... or any type of spoilers in any of my blurbs. Everything is vague.
I want my books to be about the experience, about the shocks and the swoon and the sighs.... falling in love and remembering why you love reading.
My only goal is to deliver the best reading experience I can, spoilers ruin this for me.
PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE think of others before you post or comment anywhere.
🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏
I hope you love Miles Ever After as much as I do

I just wanted to say a very special HUGE THANK YOU to my wonderful team, Kellie Alina and Lauren.
The most supportive wonderful friends and employees that anyone could ask for.
Kellie has been with me for nearly six years and she does everything that is non writing. Manages our office, Handles our Audible books and all translations.
Alina and Lauren have been with us as brand managers for six months now and they are a dream come true.
They handle all things technology, our website, store, merchandise, run the @swansquadreads Instagram page and run the tlswan Tiktok account .... which is no easy feat because my only stipulation is that nothing sexual or swearing or sleazy is to be posted..... the exact opposite to what usually works on Tiktok.
But they have absolutely nailed everything they do, there wasn’t even a transition period, perfect from day one.
You guys only see my writing... but there is so so much that goes on behind the scenes to make things run smoothly.
Thank you girls, your support and friendship is nothing short of amazing.
Bring on more books in 2023

***DRUMROLL***
Releasing August 29th.

My Temptation

The first time I laid eyes on Henley James, I was mesmerized.

The chemistry between us was like nothing I’d ever felt.
Impeccable suit, dimpled smile. He was charming and gorgeous, sophisticated, and suave. 
He gave me his business card and asked me to call.

His dating game was strong, I was gone from his first smile and I’d love to tell you our date was a raging success . . .but it wasn’t, far from it.

I decided right there on that day that Henley James and I would forever be mortal enemies, I would never think of him again.

Three years later I bought my dream home and am so excited to meet my neighbors, that is, until I do.

Oh no! What are the chances?

It’s him. Still single, still the hottest man alive . . . and still obnoxiously sarcastic. 
He saunters around, wearing next to nothing and refuses to close the blinds while undressing at night…. Not that I ever look, of course.

I will not let myself think of him at all costs…..it could be my sanity.

My Temptation is a nightmare.

And….. that’s a wrap.
My Temptation has left my hands for the very last time….
I wrote this book until my fingers bled… six times to be exact.
Yes, you read that right. I wrote My Temptation six times to get it just how it was meant to be.
Henley James was a hard nut to crack, the good ones always are 😍
And It was worth every second ❤️
I hope you love it as much as I do… 
releasing August 29th
